Date: Wed, 3 Jun 1998 13:20:54 +0530
From: Dr M.J. Wysocki <wysocki@who.ernet.in>

It is probably a little risky to say that "diabetes..... is caused by a
virus that is spreading across the country by cross-infection between
schoolchildren", as stated in [the news report on ProMED-mail of 2 June
1998. The etiology of type 1 diabetes is still not clear, and Coxsackie B4
virus seems to be only one of the elements in this etiologic puzzle.
--
M.J. Wysocki
World Health Organization
WHO,SEARO, New Delhi
e-mail: wysocki@who.ernet.in
